snippet.textDisplay: To all Indian and Pakistani bigots out here, please do some research on the origins of 'Hindustani classical' music and stop imposing your own nationalistic ideologies on each other. Music in our region has been evolving over centuries, with influences from all parts of Asia and Middle east. Mughal's also brought along with them Sufi/Turkic and Persian music which co-evolved(if there is such a word) with the music of Hindustan's indigenous people. What you hear today, is a combination of Mughlai and Indigenous Indian music.  FYI The Hindi and Urdu word; sitar originally derives from Persian seh + tar, literally meaning "three strings."
snippet.textOriginal: To all Indian and Pakistani bigots out here, please do some research on the origins of 'Hindustani classical' music and stop imposing your own nationalistic ideologies on each other. What you hear today, is a combination of Mughlai and Indigenous Indian music.  FYI The Hindi and Urdu word; sitar originally derives from Persian seh + tar, literally meaning "three strings."
